The Ogun State government on Friday sealed two gas plants and a sales outlet in Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital This followed a series of gas explosions experienced in Abeokuta within 10 days, which killed about 10 persons and injured some others.  Barely 24 hours after a gas explosion killed one person at the Olusegun Obasanjo Presidential Library in Abeokuta on Thursday, another explosion at a construction company in the city injured two persons. The state government had on Thursday constituted a Special Committee on Gas Explosion to investigate the cases of gas explosion in Abeokuta. See Also






